      "domain": "SAUDI CORPORATES (telecom)",
      "master_desc": "an illustrative Saudi telecom operator's face lines (seeded from Etihad Etisalat / Mobily FY2024), current/non-current presentation, IFRS as endorsed in KSA",
      "entity_noun": "company",
      "mapping_hints": "CORPORATE/TELECOM VOCABULARY: 'Revenue' less 'Cost of revenue' gives 'Gross profit'; 'Right of use assets' and 'Lease liabilities' arise under IFRS 16 and are split current/non-current; 'Contract assets', 'Contract costs' and 'Contract liabilities' are IFRS 15 lines, each split current/non-current; 'Short term Murabaha' is a current investment of surplus cash; 'Zakat and income tax' is a single combined line (payable on the SOFP, charge on the P&L); 'Provision for employees' end of service benefits' is a non-current obligation; 'Due from / Due to related parties' are distinct from trade receivables/payables; the SAME nature (borrowings, lease liabilities, contract assets/costs/liabilities, financial & other assets/liabilities) appears TWICE, split by maturity into current and non-current — these are DISTINCT concepts, not duplicates.",
      "extension_examples": "'Contract assets', 'Right of use assets', 'Provision for decommissioning', 'Spectrum licences'"
    },
